MatchedObjectDescriptor.QualificationSummary:
All qualification and time-in-grade (if applicable) requirements must be met within 30 days of the closing date of this announcement. You must meet the minimum qualification requirements as stated in the Office of Personnel Management (OPM) Operating Manual, Qualification Standards for General Schedule Positions, http://www.opm.gov/qualifications/Standards/group-stds/gs-prof.asp. Basic Requirement: Applicants must be a graduate of an accredited law school and must be active members of the bar of the highest court of a State, U.S. commonwealth, U.S. territory, or the District of Columbia. Applicants must possess excellent academic and professional credentials, and outstanding professional references. Specialized Experience: GS-14 - In addition to meeting the basic requirement, applicants shall have professional legal experience in excess of 3 years that is commensurate with the duties and responsibilities of the position to be filled. Specialized experience must be documented in your resume. Specialized experience includes:
(1) Experience providing legal advice and services to management clients and individual staff members on Federal employment matters, including Federal statutes, regulations, and rule- making documents such as: Title VII of the Civil Rights Act, Equal Pay Act, Rehabilitation Act/ADA, ADEA, GINA, Federal Sector Labor-Management Relations Statute, FECA, CSRA, and/or FLSA;
(2) Experience conducting legal research to gather and interpret information, identify and analyze legal issues, and ensure accuracy of details using resources such as internal and external documents, archives, electronic databases, and interviews;
(3) Experience negotiating with third parties on behalf of clients; and,
(4) Experience preparing legal documents and presentations, such as: legal briefs, motions and pleadings, negotiated agreements, issue papers, legal opinions, and memoranda with analysis and recommendations; and,
(5) Experience litigating cases before administrative bodies or Federal courts, or assisting senior attorneys as part of a trial team. GS-15 - In addition to meeting the basic requirement, applicants shall have professional legal experience in excess of 3 years that is commensurate with the duties and responsibilities of the position to be filled. Specialized experience must be documented in your resume. Specialized experience includes:
(1) Experience providing legal advice and services to management clients and individual staff members on Federal employment matters, including Federal statutes, regulations, and rule- making documents such as: Title VII of the Civil Rights Act, Equal Pay Act, Rehabilitation Act/ADA, ADEA, GINA, Federal Sector Labor-Management Relations Statute, FECA, CSRA, and/or FLSA;
(2) Experience advising senior clients and subject-matter experts in large organizations about complex employment law issues affecting all, or significant portions of, a large and diverse work force;
(3) Experience conducting legal research to gather and interpret information, identify and analyze legal issues, and ensure accuracy of details using resources such as internal and external documents, archives, electronic databases, and interviews;
(4) Experience negotiating with third parties on behalf of clients. Volunteer Experience: Experience refers to paid and unpaid experience, including volunteer work done through National Service programs (e.g., Peace Corps, AmeriCorps) and other organizations (e.g., professional, philanthropic, religious, spiritual, community, student, social). Volunteer work helps build critical competencies, knowledge, and skills, and can provide valuable training and experience that translates to paid employment. You will receive credit for all qualifying experience, including volunteer experience.
